hread is to categorize these different approaches.  This is not an endorsement of any of these.  Individual <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, including the author, may embrace multiple approaches, and may not endorse every element of each approach.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  1. Don't Worry, Be Happy:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are just fine, pets, nukes, and utility are fair, only bugs and small fixes are necessary.  These may include: Lowering the level of Anti-Summoned nukes so they are useful, fix damage shields on fire and epic pets so they do not take so long to activate, Frenzied Burnout, charm/fear pet bugs, fix AA Class Skills so they are more appealling, increase level of right-click effects on Velious armors<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  2. Improve Pet Power:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> lack power post-50, and especially on raids.  Their damage output should be increased through a combination one of more of: Modest increase in pet level and statistics, improved combat table, improved pet buffs, summoned pet only weapons and items, &quot;bane&quot; pets for raids, AAXP skill, improved <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Frenzy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, make <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Valiant Companion</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> undispellable<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  3. Reduce Pathing Consequences:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Bad pathing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is the bane of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and prevents us from using pets in many situations.  While <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are not responsible for bad pathing, they pay the price.  Reduce the consequences of bad pathing by: Fix specific bad pathing in zones, make pets indifferent to Mobs, add <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet drag</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that uses either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /corpse</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /follow</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> code to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;drag&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nearby pet along instead of pathing, modify movement algorithm for pet so that it uses existing pathing differently, improve or replace pathing mechanism for all NPCs, AAXP Skill to assume direct control of pet ala <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Eye of Zomm</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, make <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the default behavior until <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  4. Reduce Pet Penalties:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pay an enormous cost to have pets, which are not as useful as they ought to be.  In order to balance this:  Eliminate Pet experience penalty soloing and in groups, allow <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to zone, keep pets when returning from linkdeath, retrieve equipment given to pets, give <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a basic escape spell such as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Root, Fear, Snare</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or a workable emergency pet, another defensive self-buff such as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Rune</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  5. Increased Direct Damage:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Pets will never be fixed, will remain weak, and never be worth the risk on raids, so instead increase the efficacy of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nukes: increase damage, reduce mana cost, Bane/Lure nukes, Cold based nukes, Stun nuke, AAXP skill to debuff enemy, fix specific nukes, add &quot;missing&quot; nukes at awkward levels, tweak existing nukes<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  6. Better Summons:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Many summons are sub-par for their level, and several are available on items wielded by other classes.  In order to have <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>useful</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> summons: lower level of some summons, add stats to current summons, add new summons, weapons with procs, stat jewelry and armor, potions or other consumables<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  7. Better Utility:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If post-50 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are intended to be a support class, give us something <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>vital</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to do other than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Call of the Hero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Rods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Give us some new and exciting spells: Anti-Summoning Shield, Summon Foe (You Will Not Evade me Trakanon), Summon Monster (summon a random Charmed Mob), Charm Summoned, Dire Charm Summoned, Post Epic Pet, More Cool Mage Only Items<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Did I forget anyone?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I tried to include every idea I have come across recently, even if I do not agree.  I am however, only human.  Perhaps an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Erudite</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  High Elf</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> might recall something I missed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  The purpose of this list is to narrow our focus.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
What we do <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> want is for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to pick and choose among these various proposals.  The end result would likely  be both incoherent and ultimately unsatisfying.  We must take charge now, while the opportunity exists.  Are there things on this list we can simply eliminate?  Which elements enjoy the broadest consensus?  How broad or narrow a petition should we propose?  What should we attempt to get now, instead of later?  Are there severe problems prior to 50?  Is the post-50 game adequate?  Do our weaknesses only appear post-60?<br>
<br>
I look forward to your responses.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Summoner of the 59th Bottle of Beer on the Wall, and Abuser of EZCodes<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Ancient Fellowship, Xev</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
